00:18:19.600 --> 00:18:26.279
oversees that. I did talk with Kathleen Merrigan
and I said the commodity system has to change

00:18:26.279 --> 00:18:31.220
and she said pick your battles so I think
that that's going to be a tough one but if

00:18:31.220 --> 00:18:38.740
we could do, if there was a grassroots campaign
in this country that would get people all

00:18:38.740 --> 00:18:43.440
over the country to say we want better food
for kids then that would make it a priority

00:18:43.440 --> 00:18:48.610
to the Senate and the Congress people and
the Representatives who are actually the ones

00:18:48.610 --> 00:18:54.610
that vote on and decide on like staying on
the Farm Bill because the USDA promotes it,

00:18:54.610 --> 00:19:00.780
the President promotes but when Congress meet
with Representatives and especially with any

00:19:00.780 --> 00:19:06.480
kind of partisanship decide that their state
is going to be, is not going to do so well

00:19:06.480 --> 00:19:10.510
because now we're not going to have high fructose
corn syrup in schools and what's Iowa going

00:19:10.510 --> 00:19:15.650
to do if they can't produce high fructose
corn syrup, so that's why it's so important

00:19:15.650 --> 00:19:21.580
to be able touch just regular people like
us because we are the ones that the officials

00:19:21.580 --> 00:19:30.380
supposedly listen so if we could have this
mass belief and get people to actually do

00:19:30.380 --> 00:19:34.190
it, I mean when the Organic Standards was
originally going to be passed it was going

00:19:34.190 --> 00:19:41.390
to allow GMA's, irradiated food, and sewage
sludge as all part of the organic program,

00:19:41.390 --> 00:19:45.429
and there were two hundred and sixty thousand
people who wrote in and said that's ridiculous

00:19:45.429 --> 00:19:49.340
and they changed and that was before email
